    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The `flask` CLI utility that ships with Flask 0.11 does not respond to the `--version` flag. I would expect the following output:\n\n``` bash\n$ flask --version\nFlask 0.11\nPython 3.5.1\n```\n\nInstead I get the following output:\n\n``` bash\n$ flask --version\nError: no such option: --version\n```\n",
